  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether combining of radiofrequency ablation (RFA)
      and cytokine-induced killer cells (CIK) transfusion can prolong survival of patients with
      cholangiocarcinoma.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective is to evaluate whether RFA followed by CIK transfusion can prolong
      survival of patients with cholangiocarcinoma.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
